Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Expansive Kitchen with Partial Fit Out

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Located metres from Chatswood Interchange and Train Station, this double storey, fitted restaurant with existing liquor licence, outdoor seating and loading dock, is ready to occupy. 

* Ground floor – 107sqm *
* First floor – 316sqm *
* First floor outdoor terrace – 28sqm *
* Loading dock/car space – 23sqm *
* Grease trap and exhaust extraction, cool & freezer rooms, bar area plus select kitchen equipment in place
* Air conditioned throughout
* Toilet facilities on both levels 
* Excellent signage opportunities on both Victoria Avenue Mall and Post Office Lane
* Surrounded by national retailers, food & beverage operators, service providers and opposite iconic pub The Orchard Tavern.

Previously tenanted by Tawandang Thai Restaurant, the premises would suit a restaurant, licensed bar or can be stripped back for general retail or showroom use. 

For further details or to arrange an inspection, please call Amy Pfeiffer 0401 198 401.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: EXCEPTIONALLY WELL-LOCATED RESTAURANT WITH OUTDOOR DINING

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE are delighted to present 55 Alleyne Street, Chatswood to market for Sale via an On-site Auction at 10:00am on the 5th March 2021.

The property represents a rare opportunity to acquire a traditional freehold industrial asset in the tightly held Chatswood precinct. 

Key property features include:

• Two Storey freestanding building with basement car parking 
 - Internal Lettable area 421sqm*  
 - Land area 499sqm*
• Basement car parking for approx. 14 vehicles
• Prime location in the tightly held Chatswood Industrial/Bulky Goods precinct
• Prime Street exposure
• Only 10km from the Sydney CBD with easy access to the M2 and Sydney Airport
• First time offered in 35 years 
• Currently used as automotive workshop

The property is being sold via an Auction held on-site, Friday 5th March 2021 at 10:00am

For further information please contact the exclusive CBRE agents.

Ideal for Owner Occupiers or Investors

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:

Unit 24-25, 380 Eastern Valley Way, Chatswood benefits from the following key investment highlights:

-	Total area: 1,008sqm*, warehouse: 770sqm* and office: 228sqm*
-	Ideal 23.6% office and 76.3% warehouse split
-	10 car spaces
-	Short term lease, accomodating owner occupiers and investors
-	High clearance warehouse of 6.4m* to 7.5m* suitable for pallet racking
-	Clearspan warehouse with large electric roller door access 
-	Three phase power
-	Facilitates large trucks
-	Within a thriving industrial estate with an incoming Woolworths nearby
-	9km* north of the Sydney CBD with ample transport offerings along Eastern Valley Way


For further information, please contact the exclusive CBRE selling agents.
